SIMPLE: luggage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Luggage
<hw>Lug"gage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From 4th
<er>Lug</er>.]</ety> <def>That which is lugged; anything cumbrous and
heavy to be carried; especially, a traveler's trunks, baggage, etc., or
their contents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am gathering up my <qex>luggage</qex>, and preparing for my
journey.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What do you mean,⟦br⟧
To dote thus on such <qex>luggage</qex>!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Plunder; baggage.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Luggage van</b></col>, <cd>a vehicle for carrying
luggage; a railway car, or compartment of a car, for carrying
luggage.</cd> <mark>[Eng.]</mark> -- <col><b>Luggage
compartment</b></col>, <cd>the compartment in a train, bus or other
vehicle designed for storage of luggage during a journey. Separate from
the <contr>passenger compartment</contr>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lugger</ent>⟦br⟧
